Email Etiquette Checklist:

- Use a clear and relevant subject line
- Start with a professional greeting (Dear Sir/Madam)
- Keep the email concise and to the point
- Use polite and respectful language
- Avoid slang, emojis, or informal words
- Structure the email properly (introduction, body, conclusion)
- Clearly state your purpose
- Check grammar and spelling before sending
- Use a proper sign-off (Sincerely, Regards)
- Include your name and basic details
